definitions.definition: A senior administrative official in a diocese , just under the bishop , often in charge of an archdeaconry . As a title, it can be filled by either a deacon or priest.

main_definition: ( Anglicanism , Eastern Orthodoxy ) A senior administrative official in a diocese , just under the bishop , often in charge of an archdeaconry . As a title, it can be filled by either a deacon or priest.
